Sentencas: Perovskite-type SrMoO3 (SMO) is composited with commonly used electrolytes Y0.08Zr0.92O2 (YSZ), La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (LSGM) and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 (GDC) to form dual-phase materials, which are characterized as potential anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Optimization of strontium molybdate based composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Introduction of any of the electrolytes YSZ, LSGM and GDC can remarkably enhance the electrochemical performance of SrMoO3.
Titulo: Optimization of strontium molybdate based composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the composite anode in a symmetrical cell decreases in the sequence of SMO LSGM, SMO YSZ and SMO GDC.
Titulo: Optimization of strontium molybdate based composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Titulo: Optimization of strontium molybdate based composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SMO-60GDC composite shows the lowest polarization resistance of 0.107 Omega cm(2) at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Optimization of strontium molybdate based composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With SMO-60GDC composite as anode, the maximum power densities of 584, 452 and 257 mW cm(-2) are achieved at 900, 850 and 800 degrees C, respectively, for LSGM electrolyte supported cell with La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 as cathode.
Titulo: Optimization of strontium molybdate based composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell exhibits considerably stable performance under a constant voltage of 0.71 V at 800 degrees C in a short-term cycle test.
